revision.text:
[[File:A3_problem_solving_worksheet.jpg|thumb|Example of a worksheet for structured problem solving and continuous improvement]]
'''A3 problem solving''' is a structured problem-solving and continuous-improvement approach, first employed at [[Toyota]] and typically used by [[lean manufacturing]] practitioners.<ref name="Books">{{harvnb|Shook|2008}}; {{harvnb|Sobek|Smalley|2008}}; {{harvnb|Matthews|2011}}</ref> It provides a simple and strict procedure that guides problem solving by workers. The approach typically uses a single sheet of [[ISO 216|ISO A3]]-size paper, which is the source of its name.<ref name="Books"/>

